# Numbers — Memory Drill

## Purpose

Drill digit → Greek number word and reverse. Numbers are 100% arbitrary — no derivation possible, must be recalled from memory. Currently in /learn/essentials as reference only; no timed production drill exists.

Target: 3 seconds digit → word.

## Core sets

### Set A: 1–10 (drill to automaticity before Set B)
| Digit | Greek |
|-------|-------|
| 1 | ένα / μία (neuter/feminine) |
| 2 | δύο |
| 3 | τρία / τρεις |
| 4 | τέσσερα / τέσσερις |
| 5 | πέντε |
| 6 | έξι |
| 7 | εφτά / επτά |
| 8 | οχτώ / οκτώ |
| 9 | εννέα / εννιά |
| 10 | δέκα |

### Set B: 11–20
| Digit | Greek |
|-------|-------|
| 11 | έντεκα |
| 12 | δώδεκα |
| 13 | δεκατρία |
| 14 | δεκατέσσερα |
| 15 | δεκαπέντε |
| 16 | δεκαέξι |
| 17 | δεκαεφτά |
| 18 | δεκαοχτώ |
| 19 | δεκαεννέα |
| 20 | είκοσι |

### Set C: Decades (secondary)
| Digit | Greek |
|-------|-------|
| 30 | τριάντα |
| 40 | σαράντα |
| 50 | πενήντα |
| 60 | εξήντα |
| 70 | εβδομήντα |
| 80 | ογδόντα |
| 90 | ενενήντα |
| 100 | εκατό |

## Drill format

**Forward**: digit display → type Greek word
**Reverse**: Greek word → type digit (fast recognition)

No paradigm table. Sequential or random order. Could add: number reading in context ("I am __ years old" → "Έχω πέντε χρόνια").

## Agreement note (for future expansion)

1, 3, 4 have gender agreement (ένας/μία/ένα, τρεις/τρία, τέσσερις/τέσσερα). Do NOT drill agreement forms in this drill — that is a separate grammar concern. Drill the neuter form as the canonical number for now.

## Notes

- 7, 8, 9 have two accepted forms — accept both, show canonical (εφτά, οχτώ, εννέα preferred in speech)
- Build order: Set A → Set B → Set C
- Real-world anchors to show after correct answer: "Κάνει πέντε ευρώ" / "Έχω τριάντα χρόνια" — bridges number recall to sentence production
